Html:
Ok, I figured out how to add multiple images in a single table cell, however, it inserts a paragraph tag (Â¶) after each image.  Since I want the images side by side, this presents a problem.  Surely there's a line in the PHPword code that adds this paragraph tag that I can comment out.  Better yet, it would be great if it were something I could switch on/off in the addImage command.<br />
<pre><code>$table = $section-&gt;addTable();
$table-&gt;addRow();
$cell = $table-&gt;addCell(8000);
$cell-&gt;addImage('photos/image1.JPG');
$cell-&gt;addImage('photos/image2.JPG');
$cell-&gt;addImage('photos/image3.JPG');</code></pre>

Unfortunately, there's no way to do that on PHPWord 0.6.2 (CodePlex). But you can do that using Text Run on PHPWord 0.8 (<a href="https://github.com/PHPOffice/PHPWord" rel="nofollow">GitHub</a>).<br />
<pre><code>$table = $section-&gt;addTable();
$table-&gt;addRow();
$cell = $table-&gt;addCell(8000);
$textrun = $cell-&gt;createTextRun();
$textrun-&gt;addImage('photos/image1.JPG');
$textrun-&gt;addImage('photos/image2.JPG');
$textrun-&gt;addImage('photos/image3.JPG');</code></pre>

The development of PHPWord continues on GitHub. You can try the 0.8 version. It should be compatible with 0.6.2 plus tons of additional features.<br />
